lenders.name: Dom and Emma Baggayan
lenders.loan_because:
Since Typhoon Haiyan also known as Yolanda hit Philippines last year and has left many homes and businesses struggling to recover. We have decided to take this step to reach out to people all over the world to help us prepare for this devastating calamity by building a stronger infrastructure that can withstand a super typhoon.

Our vision: Entrepreneurs (Negosyante) Hub 



Due to drastic climate change we are experiencing in the Philippines and all over the world, we want to be prepared together with my local community to survive vigorous winds and heavy rain fall in the future.  We have taken the step of taking a loan because we are passionate in creating a building project that can endure climate change and economic trends. 

Our vision is for negosyante or small entrepreneurs such as store owners like Emma and other local businesses in the area to have a strong sense of safety in their business by creating an infrastructure and stalls where entrepreneurs can grow their business and have a decent place where they can call their own, which also invites more investors, consumers in the local community and gradually creating an economic centre in the local area.
lenders.occupational_info:
Dom and Emma are local shop business owners from the Philippines, Emma has been a shop owner for more than 60 years and Dom has also been involved in selling properties for more than 5 years. Emma’s shop has been pass down from generation to generation and has survived many storms in the past.

 Not later last year the local municipality have decided to refurbish the market stalls which left Emma and other local shop owners without any place to go, the local municipality has also invited larger business owners in the local community which caused small time shop owners like Emma to lose her customers, with Dom’s skills in selling and developing properties and a piece of land inherited from Emma’s parents, the couple have managed to put together their own stalls from their savings and later on turned it in to commercial building.

With a strong sense of helping small business owners like them in the community they came up with an idea of building a stalls to have a decent and stable place for local entrepreneurs to grow their business, invite more investors, customers and compete with larger business groups and also an infrastructure that can withstand economic and climate change. 

The idea of Entrepreneurs (Negosyante) Hub is to create a collective avenue for local business owners and customers to have a variety of local shops in one building, a place where small entrepreneurs can rent their stalls and expand their business and at the same time keep the local community spirit.
